channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Dr. Birx: Yes, We Tried to Quash the COVID Lab-Leak Theory
Chinese illegal immigrant surge at US southern border ‘proves our worst fears’: lawmakers
item.description: Republican lawmakers are sounding the alarm about a surge in Chinese nationals at the southern border

item.title: Rep. Fallon to Newsmax: Fauci 'a Bureaucratic Partisan Hack'
item.description: Rep. Pat Fallon, R-Texas, told Newsmax on Tuesday that Dr. Anthony Fauci's testimony before Congress this week shows that he was "a bureaucratic partisan hack" during his time on the job.

item.title: Hilarious: Joni Ernst Nails Biden With What May Be Best Hot Mic Moment Ever
Republicans hammer defiant AG Garland to hand over Biden-Hur audio
item.description: Attorney General Merrick Garland fended off Republican demands for the DOJ to hand over a recording of President Biden's interview with Robert Hur.

item.title: Jason Miller to Newsmax: Attorney General Garland 'Lying' to US
item.description: Jason Miller, a senior adviser to former President Donald Trump, Tuesday on Newsmax accused Attorney General Merrick Garland, who is testifying before the House Judiciary Committee, of "flat and simple lying to the American public."

item.title: House Speaker Mike Johnson Rolls Out Battle Plan to Combat 'Weaponization' of Government Against Trump
Hunter Biden trial: 9 key figures who may testify
item.description: Prosecutors revealed a list of witnesses who will testify in Hunter Biden's Delaware trial for federal gun violations following special counsel David Weiss' investigation.

item.title: Rep. Mast: Invite Families of Hostages to Netanyahu Speech
item.description: Rep. Brian Mast, R-Fla. wants the families of American hostages still being held in Gaza to attend Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu's address to Congress.

item.title: Biden's Statement About Hunter Raises Questions – Is He Trying to Influence Jurors in Son's Gun Case?
Johnson lays out strategy to crack down on DOJ 'weaponization' against Trump
item.description: House Speaker Mike Johnson is channeling the power of Congress to crack down on the Department of Justice after its alleged weaponization against former President Trump.

item.title: Rep. Jim Jordan: 'Eliminate Federal Funding' for Trump Prosecutors
item.description: House Judiciary Chair Jim Jordan, R-Ohio, is floating a plan that would defund the prosecutors who have brought cases against former President Donald Trump as he seeks another term in the White House.

item.title: WATCH: CBS Trots Out 84-Year-Old Ted Koppel to Fearmonger About 'Civil War 2' If Trump Loses Election
McCarthy sidesteps question on Speaker Johnson's leadership during Capitol Hill visit
item.description: House Speaker Kevin McCarthy made a rare Capitol Hill appearance on Tuesday to commemorate the anniversary of Tiananmen Square.

item.title: AG Garland Defends Justice Department: 'I Will Not be Intimidated'
item.description: Attorney General Merrick Garland hit back at Republicans for what he described as unprecedented attacks on the Justice Department Tuesday, telling lawmakers who have sought to hold him in contempt that he will "not be intimidated."Appearing before a House panel led by...
